2. Determine the possible values of X: 0, 1, 2, 3;
3. Calculate the probability of each value separately:
   $P(X=0)=( rac{1}{5})^2× rac{1}{4}= rac{1}{100}$;
   $P(X=1)=2× rac{4}{5}× rac{1}{5}× rac{1}{4}+( rac{1}{5})^2× rac{3}{4}= rac{11}{100}$;
   $P(X=2)=2× rac{4}{5}× rac{1}{5}× rac{3}{4}+( rac{4}{5})^2× rac{1}{4}= rac{2}{5}$;
   $P(X=3)=( rac{4}{5})^2× rac{3}{4}= rac{12}{25}$;
4. List the probability distribution of X;
5. Calculate according to the mathematical expectation formula: $E(X)=0× rac{1}{100}+1× rac{11}{100}+2× rac{2}{5}+3× rac{12}{25}= rac{47}{20}$.

