4. Deduce $sin\angle AMF=sin\angle BMF$ from $ rac{S_{	riangle AFM}}{S_{	riangle BFM}}= rac{|AM|}{|BM|}$, that is $\angle AMF=\angle BMF$, the slopes of line AM and BM are opposite numbers, i.e. $k_{AM}+k_{BM}=0$;
5. Substitute the slope formula to get $ rac{y_1}{x_1-m}+ rac{y_2}{x_2-m}=0$, substitute $y_1=k(x_1-1)$ and $y_2=k(x_2-1)$ and simplify to get $2x_1x_2-(m+1)(x_1+x_2)+2m=0$;
